<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Embedded helper .app for the JUCE-based AudioEngine sidecar.

        The audio-engine sidecar lives at:
            AUDIO_HAXOR.app/Contents/Frameworks/AudioHaxorEngineHelper.app/Contents/MacOS/audio-engine

        Why a nested .app instead of bare Contents/MacOS/audio-engine?
        macOS routes most third-party AUv2 plugins through audiocomponentd via
        kAudioComponentInstantiation_LoadOutOfProcess. The plugin's UI is delivered
        as a `_RemoteAUv2ViewFactory` proxy view (from AudioToolboxCore.framework)
        whose actual NSView is shipped over an XPC connection. For audiocomponentd
        to authorize the host process and complete the audit-token handshake, the
        host must look like a real Cocoa application — its own bundle, its own
        Info.plist, its own bundle identifier, its own NSApp activation context.

        A bare Mach-O sibling of the main `audio-haxor` binary inside Contents/MacOS/
        does NOT qualify: [NSBundle mainBundle] for that process resolves up the
        directory tree and returns the parent AUDIO_HAXOR.app, so audiocomponentd
        considers it part of the main app and the XPC view delivery either stalls
        or returns the 1×1 placeholder NSView indefinitely (permanently blank
        plugin editor windows).

        Wrapping in a nested .app fixes this: [NSBundle mainBundle] from the helper
        binary now stops at this Info.plist, the helper has its own bundle ID, and
        audiocomponentd treats it as a distinct host that can receive XPC plugin
        view deliveries.

        LSUIElement=true makes this an "agent" app — no Dock icon, no menu bar at
        startup. The helper transitions to a regular foreground app at runtime via
        juce::Process::makeForegroundProcess() (NSApplicationActivationPolicyRegular)
        when an AU plugin editor window opens.

        See scripts/postbundle-audio-engine-helper.sh for the bundling pipeline and
        audio-engine/README.md "Helper .app architecture" for the full rationale.
    -->
    <key>CFBundleDevelopmentRegion</key>
    <string>en</string>
    <key>CFBundleExecutable</key>
    <string>audio-engine</string>
    <key>CFBundleIdentifier</key>
    <string>com.menketechnologies.audio-haxor.audio-engine-helper</string>
    <key>CFBundleInfoDictionaryVersion</key>
    <string>6.0</string>
    <key>CFBundleName</key>
    <string>AudioHaxorEngineHelper</string>
    <key>CFBundlePackageType</key>
    <string>APPL</string>
    <key>CFBundleShortVersionString</key>
    <string>1.0</string>
    <key>CFBundleVersion</key>
    <string>1</string>
    <key>LSMinimumSystemVersion</key>
    <string>10.15</string>
    <key>LSUIElement</key>
    <true/>
    <key>NSHighResolutionCapable</key>
    <true/>
    <key>NSPrincipalClass</key>
    <string>NSApplication</string>
</dict>
</plist>
